  <prompt>
    Add a new `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade interface in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` per Q11 binding decision
    (cleaner than extending `IWorkspacePrefillAi`). The facade wraps
    `IPlaybookOrchestrationService` so CRUD-side callers (chat tool in task 021;
    M365 Copilot agent gateway; future R7+ consumers) never inject the orchestration
    service directly ‚ÄĒ preserving the ADR-013 facade boundary.

    Critical-path context: ADR-013 binding rule from project CLAUDE.md "MUST NOT inject
    `IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`, `IPlaybookOrchestrationService`, or other
    AI-internal types directly into CRUD-side code." This facade is the canonical way
    chat-tool code (task 021) reaches the playbook execution engine.

    Confirmation Trigger: per project CLAUDE.md ¬ßConfirmation Triggers ‚ÄĒ "Any task
    modifies a public contract surface in `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/`" ‚ÄĒ PAUSE for
    user confirmation before merging.

    Interface shape: `Task&lt;PlaybookInvocationResult&gt; InvokePlaybookAsync(string playbookId, IDictionary&lt;string, object&gt; parameters, InvocationContext context, CancellationToken ct)`.
    Implementation delegates to the existing orchestration service; this task ships the
    interface + implementation skeleton + DI registration. Task 021 builds the actual
    chat tool that consumes the facade.

    Reuse patterns from existing facades in `PublicContracts/`: `IWorkspacePrefillAi`,
    `IInsightsAi`, `IInvoiceAi`, `IBriefingAi`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with deep `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` familiarity and ADR-013
    facade-boundary discipline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade interface + thin implementation exists in
    `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/`. Implementation delegates to
    `IPlaybookOrchestrationService` (AI-internal). DI registered inside existing
    `AnalysisServicesModule`. Unit tests cover: facade exposes only safe surface; CRUD-side
    cannot inject orchestration internals through it. Build green; publish-size delta
    reported.
  </goal>

